Atmospheres Node The PDS Atmospheres node is the primary delivery point for CIRS data, which can be found here: https://pds-atmospheres.nmsu.edu/data_and_services/atmospheres_data/Cassini/inst-cirs.html.

In SvF- technology the basic tool for solving independent mathematical programming problems in parallel is the Everest optimization service [13, 14] based on Everest toolkit [15], http://everest.distcomp.org .

Section 4 presents main aspects of the SvF{method software implementa- tion: usage of Pyomo package (Python Optimization Modeling Objects), http://www.pyomo.org ; special symbolic notation that simplies formulation of the model and regularization rule; dis- cretization of dierential and integral equations if they are present in the model; usage of Everest optimization service.
There are a number of services available at the URL https://optmod.distcomp.org .

This computing environment is extensible because the potential users can add their own computing resources to the optimization environment via the open source Everest agent http://everest.distcomp.org/docs .

Now the service provides unied access to the following solvers, allowing to solve the main types of mathematical programming problems (LP/MILP/NLP/MINLP): Ipopt (Coin-OR Interior Point Optimizer, NLP), https://github.com/coin-or/Ipopt ; CBC (Coin-OR Branch-and-Cut, LP, MILP), https://github.com/coin-or/Cbc ; SCIP (Solving Constraint Integer Programs, LP, MILP, MINLP), http://scip.zib.de ; Bonmin (COIN-OR Basic Open-source Nonlinear (convex) Mixed Integer programming, MINLP), https://github.com/coin-or/Bonmin .

Besides, we are working on implementation of an analogue of AMPLX (an extension of AMPL-scripting to exchange data with Everest optimization services, [13]) on the base of Py- omo - so called PyomoEverest, https://github.com/distcomp/pyomo-everest .

The following problems were studied (see poster at https://www.researchgate.net/ publication/334523588 ): F) The estimation of distribution and sources of the atmospheric aerosol pollution (PM10) in the North of France.
Optionally, optimization ser- vices [13] of extensible computing environment https://optmod.distcomp.org based on Everest toolkit [15] may be used as well.
